@17 = ~Auril's Touch~
@18 = ~Auril’s Touch (Necromancy)
Sphere: Elemental, Combat
Level: 1
Range: Touch
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: Instant
Area of Effect: Creature Touched
Saving Throw: Neg.

The caster attempts to replicate the touch of the goddess Auril, the Frostmaiden and delivers it to the victim. With a successful melee attack, the affected creature receives 6d12 cold damage as well as a -4 penalty to its THAC0. The touched creature must also make a saving throw vs. death or be instantly frozen upon touch.~

@19 = ~Winter's Lament~
@20 = ~Winter's Lament (Enchantment/Charm)
Sphere: Charm, Elemental, Combat
Level: 3
Range: Visual sight of the caster
Duration: Delayed
Casting Time: Instant
Area of Effect: 30-ft. radius
Saving Throw: Special

The caster hymns the song known as the Winter's Lament. The Winter's Lament however, is not a song but rather a culmination all the emotions of sorrow, fear and despair that a grievous winter's storm brings. Everyone in the area of its effect is overwhelmed with the horrid emotions assailing their senses as well as the feel of that one fateful winter. The victims suffer 6d12 + 10d12 cold damage as well as being severely hindered of movement. They will also be afflicted with confusion or morale failure or may instantly die (saving throw negates.)

The caster however, must remain still while singing for the duration of the song. Due to the nature of this dreadful spell, the caster is physically drained and she will likely require rest immediately afterwards, as it will cause days worth of fatigue almost instantaneously.~

